OL,3,CManchester to fall silent as city
OL,4,Cmarks nine years since terror attack
OL,6,FManchester will fall silent to mark
OL,7,Fthe ninth anniversary of the arena
OL,8,Fterror bombing, with tributes planned
OL,9,Facross the city to remember the 22
OL,10,Fpeople who lost their lives.
OL,12,FTwo separate minute-long silences are
OL,13,Fset to be observed at Victoria Station
OL,14,Fas residents, survivors, and families
OL,15,Fcome together in remembrance.
OL,17,FThe city council confirmed that the
OL,18,Fperiod of silence will be held twice
OL,19,Fthroughout Friday: first at noon and
OL,20,Fagain at 10:31pm - the exact time the
OL,21,Fbomb was detonated.
